      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a strict JSON generator.\n\nCurrent date and time (use this to resolve relative dates): {{ $now.toISO() }}\n\nAnalyze the following email and assign one or more labels from this list. An email CAN have multiple labels, EXCEPT \"Spam\" which is always exclusive — if Spam applies, return ONLY [\"Spam\"] and nothing else.\n\n- \"Urgent\" → needs my attention or a reply soon: overdue bills, security alerts, anything someone is actively waiting on me for.\n- \"College/TnP\" → emails from college groups, the Training & Placement cell, or teachers.\n- \"Opportunities\" → anything tied to a job, internship, hackathon, or competition I am already engaged with: application/registration confirmations, status updates (profile viewed, shortlisted, interview scheduled, accepted, rejected), or logistics (schedule changes, results, prize announcements).\n- \"Bills & Subscriptions\" → bills, receipts, payment confirmations, subscription renewals.\n- \"Informational\" → general updates, shipping/delivery alerts, social notifications, and job/hackathon RECOMMENDATION digests for things I have NOT applied to.\n- \"Spam\" → promotional or marketing junk with no real value.\n\nAlso detect whether the email references a specific date, deadline, or event (an interview, a meeting, a due date, a hackathon date, a deadline to respond). If so, set hasEvent to true and extract eventTitle (a short label) and eventDateTime (full ISO 8601 with timezone offset, e.g. 2026-06-29T18:00:00+05:30 — resolve relative phrases like \"tomorrow\" or \"in 3 days\" using the current date/time given above). If there is no specific date, set hasEvent to false and omit eventTitle/eventDateTime.\n\nDetermine whether this email requires a reply from me.\nSet replyNeeded to true if:\n- The sender is asking a question.\n- A confirmation is requested.\n- A response is expected.\n- Someone is waiting for my action.\nOtherwise return false.\n\nSummary: extract the most important information into 1 sentence, not more than 4000 characters.\n\nReturn your response as a JSON object, **only using** this exact format:\n{ \"labels\": [\"<one or more of the categories above>\"], \"summary\": \"<Summary>\", \"hasEvent\": <true or false>, \"eventTitle\": \"<title, omit if hasEvent is false>\", \"eventDateTime\": \"<ISO datetime, omit if hasEvent is false>\" }\n\nExample (multi-label, with event):\n{ \"labels\": [\"Urgent\", \"Opportunities\"], \"summary\": \"Tech Corp has shortlisted you for a technical interview and asks you to confirm a slot by Friday.\", \"hasEvent\": true, \"replyNeeded\":true, \"eventTitle\": \"Tech Corp interview slot confirmation deadline\", \"eventDateTime\": \"2026-06-26T23:59:00\" }\n\nRules:\n- Do NOT return markdown (no triple backticks, no ```json)\n- Use double quotes for keys and string values\n- Do NOT include explanations, extra text, or formatting\n- Return ONLY the one JSON object described above, replacing values as needed\n\nReview your response to ensure you meet the rules before you generate the output.\n\nEmail content:\nSubject: {{ $json.subject }}\nFrom: {{ $json.from }}\n\nBody:\n{{ $json.text.substring(0, 1500) }}\n",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {}
      },
